@startuml
title Dagents OCaml Adoption - System Context

skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false

actor "Watchdog" as Watchdog
actor "Datalytics" as Datalytics

rectangle "Dagents Framework" {
  component "Spring Boot\nCore Service" as Core
  component "Python\nPipeline Service" as Pipeline
  component "Python\nModel Service" as Model
  component "LMA\n(source-level model runs)" as LMA
  component "GMA\n(assimilated-data model runs)" as GMA

  package "OCaml Functional Kernel" {
    component "Pipeline Compiler" as OCamlPipeline
    component "Dataset Compiler" as OCamlDataset
    component "Model Router" as OCamlRouter
    component "Manifest Compiler" as OCamlManifest
  }
}

cloud "Kubernetes Cluster" as K8s

Watchdog --> Core : parameterized workload intents
Watchdog --> LMA : source data + source policies
Watchdog --> GMA : aggregate data + global policies

Datalytics --> Core : workload intents
Datalytics --> LMA : source data
Datalytics --> GMA : aggregate data

Core --> OCamlManifest : compile workload specs
Pipeline --> OCamlPipeline : compile DAGs
LMA --> OCamlDataset : profile source datasets
LMA --> OCamlRouter : choose source models
GMA --> OCamlDataset : profile assimilated datasets
GMA --> OCamlRouter : choose aggregate models

Pipeline --> Model : execute planned ML jobs
LMA --> Model : run source-level jobs
GMA --> Model : run aggregate jobs
Core --> K8s : emit manifests for Deployments/Jobs/CronJobs

note right of OCamlManifest
Deterministic manifest generation
from typed workload specs
end note

note bottom of OCamlRouter
One routing engine shared by
LMA and GMA
end note

@enduml
